    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">554.A2/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Italian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Martino</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to your note of August 2, 1927,
                    inviting the Government of the United States to participate in the International
                    Conference on Copyright to open at Rome on May 8 next,<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d303fn40">The Conference had been postponed from October
                        1927.</note> I have the honor now to inform you that, after reconsideration,
                    it has been decided to accept the invitation and that the Honorable Henry P.
                    Fletcher, American Ambassador at Rome, Mr. Thorvald Soltterg, Register of
                    Copyrights, Library of Congress, and the Honorable Sol Bloom, Member of
                    Congress, have been designated to attend the Congress as delegates on the part
                    of the United States. <pb facs="0528" n="400" xml:id="pg_400"/> The American
                    Ambassador at Rome was instructed by cable on April 25<note n="42"
                        xml:id="d303fn42">Not printed.</note> to advise your Government
                    accordingly.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank B. Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
